<annotation encoding="math/tex">\begin{align*}
 \vec{p}&amp; = m\vec{v} \\ 
 &amp; = \left(\text{0,16}\right)\left(40\right) \\ 
 &amp; = \text{6,4}\text{ kg·m·s^{-1}} \\ 
 &amp; = \text{6,4}\text{ kg·m·s^{-1}}&nbsp;\text{in the direction of the batsman} 
\end{align*}</annotation></semantics></math></div><div class="solution" data-class="workstep" data-type="Step">


<div class="title">Quote the final answer</div><p>The momentum of the cricket ball is <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics>
  <mtext>6,4</mtext>
<annotation encoding="math/tex">\text{6,4}</annotation></semantics></math>~<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics>
  <mtext>kg·m·s^{-1}</mtext>
<annotation encoding="math/tex">\text{kg·m·s^{-1}}</annotation></semantics></math>&nbsp;in the direction of the batsman.</p></div></div>d</body>
